# Event Catalog ‚Äî {{PROJECT_NAME}}

> Single source of truth for every product-analytics event this app sends to PostHog.
> Keep this file in sync with actual `posthog.capture(...)` calls. The
> `observability-auditor` worker verifies that every capture call has a matching
> entry here on each verify phase.

## Naming convention

- `verb_noun` lower snake_case (e.g., `clicked_signup`, `completed_onboarding`).
- Noun first when the event is about an object, verb first when about an action.
- Never rename an event after launch ‚Äî deprecate and add a new one instead.

## Required properties (every event)

| Property | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `$user_id` | string | Set via `posthog.identify()` once user signs up/in. |
| `environment` | `"production" \| "staging" \| "development"` | Auto-set via `super_properties`. |
| `release` | string | Build SHA; inject via env var. |

## Core events

### `signed_up`
User completed account creation.

| Property | Type | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `method` | `"email" \| "google" \| "github"` | `"google"` |
| `referrer` | string? | `"marketing-site"` |

### `signed_in`
User authenticated in an existing session.

| Property | Type | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `method` | `"email" \| "google" \| "github"` | `"email"` |

### `completed_onboarding`
User finished the first-run tutorial / onboarding flow.

| Property | Type | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `steps_completed` | number | `4` |
| `duration_seconds` | number | `312` |

### `invoked_core_action`
Fires when the user performs the primary value action of your product.
**TODO**: rename to your product's actual core action (e.g., `created_order`,
`sent_message`, `published_post`). This is the single most important event ‚Äî
every other metric is derived from it.

| Property | Type | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `action_type` | string | depends on product |

## Events to add per feature

Whenever you ship a new feature, add:

1. At least one `{feature}_started` event when the user enters the feature flow.
2. At least one `{feature}_completed` event when the user reaches the success state.
3. Optionally `{feature}_abandoned` with a `reason` property when detectable.

This minimum triple lets you build a funnel and measure drop-off without custom
retro analysis.

## Do NOT send

- Raw email addresses, phone numbers, or government IDs (use the identified
  user ID instead and correlate on the PostHog side).
- Full request/response bodies from user-facing APIs (risk of PII leak).
- Passwords, tokens, or session keys under any circumstance.

